esources. You can also%0afind more by using search engines and phrases like 'Webstyle' or 'Webwriting'%0aor 'Writing for the Web'.%0a%0aTim Berners-Lee's CERN Style Guide:\\%0ahttp://www.w3.org/Provider/Style/Introduction.html%0a%0aJakob Nielsen:\\%0ahttp://www.useit.com/papers/webwriting/%0a%0aJutta Degener on writing and editing for the Web:\\%0ahttp://kbs.cs.tu-berlin.de/~jutta/index.html\\%0ahttp://kbs.cs.tu-berlin.de/~jutta/ht/writing.html%0a%0aYale Center for Advanced Instructional Media: Web Style Guide\\%0ahttp://info.med.yale.edu/caim/manual/contents.html%0a%0a%0aJoe Gillespie's Web Page Design for Designers\\%0ahttp://www.wpdfd.com/wpdhome.htm%0a%0aJeffrey Zeldman's Ask Dr. Web:\\%0ahttp://www.zeldman.com/faq.html%0a%0a%0aWeb Pages That Suck\\%0ahttp://www.webpagesthatsuck.com/%0a%0aWebmaster - Web Writing Style Resources\\%0ahttp://www.cio.com/summaries/web/content/%0a%0a%0aDavid Siegel's Net Tips for Writers & Designers (Web Wonk)\\%0ahttp://www.dsiegel.com/tips/index.html%0a%0aWorld Wide Web Unleashed (Web enhancement for print book)\\%0ahttp://www.december.com/works/wwwu.html%0a%0aCreating Killer Websites Online (Web enhancement for print book)\\%0ahttp://killersites.com/%0a%0aCrawford Kilian%0ackilian@`NOSPAMSPAMSPAMGREENEGGSBACONHAMANDSPAMhubcap.mlnet.com\\%0ahttp://www.capcollege.bc.ca/magic/cmns/crofpers.html \\%0aFiction Writer's Page: \\%0ahttp://www.capcollege.bc.ca/magic/cmns/fwp.html %0a%0a%0a%0a%0aONLINE-WRITING uses Lyris mailing list software.  http://www.lyris.com \\%0aList settings, archive: http://www.planetarynews.com/online-writing \\%0aIn-person OWL networking: http://www.planetarynews.com/networking.html \\%0a%0a----%0a%0a* Online Writing list has moved to http://talk.poynter.org/online-writing/%0a%0a%0a(:if false:)%0aSummary:an email from a colleague on writing styles%0aCategories:[[!Articles]],[[!Links]]%0aParent:(Main.)Communication%0aIncludeMe:[[Main.Communication]]%0aTags: writing, style%0a(:tags-hide writing, style:)%0a(:if:)%0